  "description": "Factory maintenance schedule for the Leapmotor T03 (BEV), extracted from its OWN official owner's manual (not inherited from B10/C10 — the T03 is a different platform). Base interval 20000 km / 12 months, whichever comes first. T03-specific differences vs B10: reducer oil 2y/20000 km (B10 is 60000 km, km-only); tires 3y/60000 km with tread limit 3 mm (B10 is 40000 km / 1.6 mm); coolant is MAINTENANCE-FREE — level check only, NO scheduled replacement (B10 replaces at 40000 km/4y); there is NO separate reducer/drivetrain filter replacement on the T03 (B10 has one at 60000 km). Brake disc wear limits: front < 18 mm, rear < 8 mm. A/C filter: clean every 6 months / 10000 km, replace every 12 months / 20000 km. Manual battery tip (not a service item): fully charge/discharge at least every 6 months or 7000 km for battery self-calibration. Tire rotation (10000 km) is stated in the manual's tire content.",
